                            The text contains the first part of the third section of E.A.W. Budge's edition, corresponding to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">67 l. 2-71 l. 2</citedRange></bibl>, with some variants (the name of Michael is replaced by that of Mary).</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3">
                          <title type="complete">First prayer for the heavenly journey, entitled ጸሎት፡ ዘመንገድ፡ ሰማይ፡</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>                          
                          <note>
                            The text contains the last part of the third section of E.A.W. Budge's edition, corresponding to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">71 ll. 8-32</citedRange></bibl>. Some words are omitted after the magic names.</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4">
                          <title type="complete">Second prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>      
                          <note>The text corresponds to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">73 l. 2-74 l. 22</citedRange></bibl>.</note>  
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.5">
                          <title type="complete">Third prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>    
                          <note>The text corresponds to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">74 l. 24-75 l. 24</citedRange></bibl>.</note>  
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.6">
                          <title type="complete">Fourth prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>  
                          <note>
                            The entire text is the following:
                          <q xml:lang="gez">
                            ፀዋጋን፡ መሃረኒ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወሥረይ፡ ሊተ፡ ኃጢአትየ፡ በዛቲ፡ ዕለት፡ ወሰውረኒ፡ ሊተ፡ እምኵሉ፡ እኩይ፡ ወመንሱት፡ መአልተ፡ ወሌሊተ፡ በእንተ፡ ስምከ፡ ዕቀበኒ፡ 
                            ሊተ፡ እምኵሉ፡ <choice><sic>ጸናህያን፡</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ጸናህያነ፡</corr></choice> ፍኖት፡ ግሩማን፡ መላእክት፡
                          </q>.</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.7">
                          <title type="complete">Fifth prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>   
                          <note>
                            The entire text is the following:
                            <q xml:lang="gez">
                              በዛቲ፡ ዕለት፡ ግርምት፡ <choice><sic>አመወት፡</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">እመውት፡</corr></choice> ወትፈልጥ፡ ነፍስየ፡ 
                              እምሥ<add place="above">ጋ</add>የ፡ አመ፡ ይመጽዑ፡ ግሩማን፡ መላእክት፡ ጽልመት፡ ፈኑ፡ ሊተ፡ መላእ<supplied reason="omitted">ክ</supplied>ት፡ ብርሃን፡
                              ወያመጽእዋ፡ ኀቤከ፡ መሃራ፡ <choice><sic>ወተሰሃላ፡</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ወተሳሃላ፡</corr></choice> 
                              <supplied reason="omitted">ለነፍስየ፡</supplied> ሊተ፡ ለገብርከ፡ ገብረ፡ ሥላሴ<supplied reason="omitted">።</supplied>
                            </q>.</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.8">
                          <title type="complete">Sixth prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/> 
                          <note>
                            The entire text is the following:
                            <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ክርስቶስ፡ ኩና፡ አቃቤ፡ <surplus>ኩና፡</surplus> ክርስቶስ፡ ኩና፡ መራሄ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ኩና፡ ረዳኤ፡ በእድ<surplus>ት</surplus>፡ ልዕልት፡ ከመ፡ 
                              <choice><sic>ይእቅብዋ፡</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ኢይእቀብዋ፡</corr></choice> ውስተ፡ ብካይ፡ ወ<del rend="expunctuated">ት</del>ኃቅየ፡
                              ስነን፡ <supplied reason="omitted">ለ</supplied>መጽሐፈ<supplied reason="omitted">፡</supplied> ዕዳሃ፡ ለነፍ<supplied reason="omitted">ስ</supplied>የ፡ ሊተ፡
                            </q>.</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.9">
                          <title type="complete">Seventh prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>         
                          <note>
                            The entire text is the following:
                            <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ንስእለከ፡ <choice><sic>ወናስተበቈአከ፡</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ወናስተበቍአከ፡</corr></choice> እምፍጥረተ፡ ዓለም፡ ወትፈልጥ፡ እባግአ፡ 
                              እምአጣሊ፡ ይእተ፡ አሚረ፡ ተዘከራ፡ እግዚኦ፡ ለነፍስየ፡ <gap reason="omitted" resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices"/> እስመ፡ ነቅእ፡ ሕይወት፡ እንተ፡ ዘበአማን፡ ወኵሉ፡
                              ዘሰአለከ፡ ነፍሳት፡ ወሃሤት፡ ኦመሃሪ፡ መሃረኒ፡ <surplus>ዘ</surplus>ሊተ፡
                            </q>.</note>
                         </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.10">
                          <title type="complete">Eighth prayer, on the names told by Jesus to Andrew</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>   
                          <note>The text corresponds to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">81 l. 26-82 l. 21</citedRange></bibl>.</note>  
                        </msItem>
                      </msItem>
